<!-- 
	Here I have placed an Example of how to Bind Multiple Equipment to a Unit.
	This is about 90% of Weapons Unleashed, It's not a terrible complex Mod.
-->

<!-- Example 1 -->
<Equipment>
	<Bind to="ExampleUnitName">
		<eqp name="EquipmentName1"/>
		<eqp name="EquipmentName2"/>
		<eqp name="EquipmentName3"/>
	</Bind>
<Equipment>

<!-- Example 2 -->
<Equipment>
	<Bind eqp="EquipmentName">
		<to name="Unit/Class"/>
		<to name="EquipmentName1"/>
		<eqp name="EquipmentName2"/>
	</Bind>
<Equipment>
<!--
	Here is another Example that has Real Names in it.
	I'm sorry if you view this File with Syntax highlighting but,
	To avoid issue this actually trying to load, I put it into a comment.

	<Bind to="Rangers">
		<eqp name="M500PP"/>
		<eqp name="M1014"/>
		<eqp name="M16A4"/>
		<eqp name="M4 Carbine"/>
		<eqp name="M4Sup"/>
		<eqp name="MK 18"/>
		<eqp name="MK 18Sup"/>
		<eqp name="M4/M203"/>
	</Bind>

	Now what does this do? well it's fairly obvious if you read it,
	but to explain it simply at the top it says '<Bind to="Rangers">'
	This sets up this whole Bind section to bind to the Rangers Unit
	
	Now this is important because it doesn't actually have to be a Unit,
	it can be a Class as well for example 'Assault' which is still the rangers.
	However it's only that one Class inside the Rangers.

	Now lets look at those other lines '<eqp name="M500PP"/>'
	This here is the name of the equipment,
	Ideally this will be the 'Firearm name="ThisThingHere">'
	This applies to other equipment types as well like Grenades,
	eplosive charges etc.

-->
